unschmedien als Grenzerfahrung vor, die sich als Paradigma medialer Selbstreflexion begreifen lässt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMotion picturesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and direction. 0aScience fiction filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aTechnology in motion picturesxHistoryy20th century. 4aKino. 4aMedien. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMediologie. 4aWunschmedium. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.  aMedia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102523008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2000-2009z97831104634080 cprintz978389942823040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839408230?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839408230423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839408230/original  a978-3-11-046340-8  transcript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2000-2009c2000d2009  a978-3-11-102523-0  transcript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2000d2009